<div data-type="exercise" id="fs-id1165043317506">
<div data-type="problem" id="fs-id1165043074826">
<p id="fs-id1165043392317">Use the first derivative test to locate all local extrema for <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mi>f</mi><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mo>=</mo><mtext>&#8722;</mtext><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>18</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>.</mo></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><mi>f</mi><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mo>=</mo><mtext>&#8722;</mtext><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>18</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>.</mo></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math></p>
</div>
<div data-type="solution" id="fs-id1165043385478">
<p id="fs-id1165043281485"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mi>f</mi></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mi>f</mi></annotation-xml></semantics></math> has a local minimum at <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mn>&#8722;2</mn></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><mn>&#8722;2</mn></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math> and a local maximum at <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn><mo>.</mo></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><mn>3</mn><mo>.</mo></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math></p>
</div>
<div data-type="commentary" id="fs-id1165042923236" data-element-type="hint"><div data-type="title">Hint</div>
<p id="fs-id1165043429519">Find all critical points of <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mi>f</mi></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mi>f</mi></annotation-xml></semantics></math> and determine the signs of <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mrow><msup><mi>f</mi><mo>&#8242;</mo></msup><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><msup><mi>f</mi><mo>&#8242;</mo></msup><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math> over particular intervals determined by the critical points.</p>
