<div data-type="example" id="fs-id1165043312782">
<div data-type="exercise" id="fs-id1165042640287">
<div data-type="problem" id="fs-id1165042479991"><div data-type="title">Using the First Derivative Test</div>
<p id="fs-id1165042319589">Use the first derivative test to find the location of all local extrema for <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mi>f</mi><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mrow><mn>1</mn><mtext>/</mtext><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup><mo>&#8722;</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mrow><mn>5</mn><mtext>/</mtext><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup><mo>.</mo></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><mi>f</mi><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mrow><mn>1</mn><mtext>/</mtext><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup><mo>&#8722;</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mrow><mn>5</mn><mtext>/</mtext><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup><mo>.</mo></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math> Use a graphing utility to confirm your results.</p>
</div>
<div data-type="solution" id="fs-id1165042369651">
<p id="fs-id1165043109175">Step 1. The derivative is</p><div data-type="equation" id="fs-id1165043066545" class="unnumbered" data-label=""><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block"><semantics><mrow><mrow><msup><mi>f</mi><mo>&#8242;</mo></msup><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>5</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac><msup><mi>x</mi><mrow><mn>&#8722;2</mn><mtext>/</mtext><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup><mo>&#8722;</mo><mfrac><mn>5</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac><msup><mi>x</mi><mrow><mn>2</mn><mtext>/</mtext><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>5</mn><mrow><mn>3</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mrow><mn>2</mn><mtext>/</mtext><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfrac><mo>&#8722;</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>5</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mrow><mn>2</mn><mtext>/</mtext><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup></mrow><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>5</mn><mo>&#8722;</mo><mn>5</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mrow><mn>4</mn><mtext>/</mtext><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mrow><mn>2</mn><mtext>/</mtext><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>5</mn><mrow><mo>(</mo><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>&#8722;</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mrow><mn>4</mn><mtext>/</mtext><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup></mrow><mo>)</mo></mrow></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mrow><mn>2</mn><mtext>/</mtext><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfrac><mo>.</mo></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><msup><mi>f</mi><mo>&#8242;</mo></msup><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>5</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac><msup><mi>x</mi><mrow><mn>&#8722;2</mn><mtext>/</mtext><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup><mo>&#8722;</mo><mfrac><mn>5</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac><msup><mi>x</mi><mrow><mn>2</mn><mtext>/</mtext><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>5</mn><mrow><mn>3</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mrow><mn>2</mn><mtext>/</mtext><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfrac><mo>&#8722;</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>5</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mrow><mn>2</mn><mtext>/</mtext><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup></mrow><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>5</mn><mo>&#8722;</mo><mn>5</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mrow><mn>4</mn><mtext>/</mtext><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mrow><mn>2</mn><mtext>/</mtext><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>5</mn><mrow><mo>(</mo><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>&#8722;</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mrow><mn>4</mn><mtext>/</mtext><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup></mrow><mo>)</mo></mrow></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mrow><mn>2</mn><mtext>/</mtext><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfrac><mo>.</mo></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math></div>
<p id="fs-id1165042514176">The derivative <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mrow><msup><mi>f</mi><mo>&#8242;</mo></msup><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><msup><mi>f</mi><mo>&#8242;</mo></msup><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math> when <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>&#8722;</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mrow><mn>4</mn><mtext>/</mtext><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>&#8722;</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mrow><mn>4</mn><mtext>/</mtext><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math> Therefore, <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mrow><msup><mi>f</mi><mo>&#8242;</mo></msup><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><msup><mi>f</mi><mo>&#8242;</mo></msup><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math> at <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mtext>&#177;</mtext><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mtext>&#177;</mtext><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math> The derivative <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mrow><msup><mi>f</mi><mo>&#8242;</mo></msup><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><msup><mi>f</mi><mo>&#8242;</mo></msup><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math> is undefined at <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math> Therefore, we have three critical points: <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>,</mo></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>,</mo></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math> <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math> and <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>&#8722;1</mn><mo>.</mo></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>&#8722;1</mn><mo>.</mo></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math> Consequently, divide the interval <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mrow><mo>(</mo><mrow><mtext>&#8722;</mtext><mi>&#8734;</mi><mo>,</mo><mi>&#8734;</mi></mrow><mo>)</mo></mrow></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><mrow><mo>(</mo><mrow><mtext>&#8722;</mtext><mi>&#8734;</mi><mo>,</mo><mi>&#8734;</mi></mrow><mo>)</mo></mrow></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math> into the smaller intervals <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mrow><mo>(</mo><mrow><mtext>&#8722;</mtext><mi>&#8734;</mi><mo>,</mo><mn>&#8722;1</mn></mrow><mo>)</mo></mrow><mo>,</mo><mrow><mo>(</mo><mrow><mn>&#8722;1</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow><mo>)</mo></mrow><mo>,</mo><mrow><mo>(</mo><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mo>)</mo></mrow><mo>,</mo></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><mrow><mo>(</mo><mrow><mtext>&#8722;</mtext><mi>&#8734;</mi><mo>,</mo><mn>&#8722;1</mn></mrow><mo>)</mo></mrow><mo>,</mo><mrow><mo>(</mo><mrow><mn>&#8722;1</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow><mo>)</mo></mrow><mo>,</mo><mrow><mo>(</mo><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mo>)</mo></mrow><mo>,</mo></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math> and <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mrow><mo>(</mo><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mi>&#8734;</mi></mrow><mo>)</mo></mrow><mo>.</mo></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><mrow><mo>(</mo><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mi>&#8734;</mi></mrow><mo>)</mo></mrow><mo>.</mo></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math></p>
<p id="fs-id1165042354821">Step 2: Since <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><msup><mi>f</mi><mo>&#8242;</mo></msup></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><msup><mi>f</mi><mo>&#8242;</mo></msup></annotation-xml></semantics></math> is continuous over each subinterval, it suffices to choose a test point <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mi>x</mi></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mi>x</mi></annotation-xml></semantics></math> in each of the intervals from step <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mn>1</mn></annotation-xml></semantics></math> and determine the sign of <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><msup><mi>f</mi><mo>&#8242;</mo></msup></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><msup><mi>f</mi><mo>&#8242;</mo></msup></annotation-xml></semantics></math> at each of these points. The points <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>&#8722;2</mn><mo>,</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>&#8722;</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>,</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>,</mo><mspace width="0.2em"/><mtext>and</mtext><mspace width="0.2em"/><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>&#8722;2</mn><mo>,</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>&#8722;</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>,</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>,</mo><mspace width="0.2em"/><mtext>and</mtext><mspace width="0.2em"/><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math> are test points for these intervals.</p>
