</tbody></table><p id="fs-id1165043062405">Step 3: Since <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mi>f</mi></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mi>f</mi></annotation-xml></semantics></math> is decreasing over the interval <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mrow><mo>(</mo><mrow><mtext>&#8722;</mtext><mi>&#8734;</mi><mo>,</mo><mn>&#8722;1</mn></mrow><mo>)</mo></mrow></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><mrow><mo>(</mo><mrow><mtext>&#8722;</mtext><mi>&#8734;</mi><mo>,</mo><mn>&#8722;1</mn></mrow><mo>)</mo></mrow></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math> and increasing over the interval <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mrow><mo>(</mo><mrow><mn>&#8722;1</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow><mo>)</mo></mrow><mo>,</mo></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><mrow><mo>(</mo><mrow><mn>&#8722;1</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow><mo>)</mo></mrow><mo>,</mo></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math> <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mi>f</mi></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mi>f</mi></annotation-xml></semantics></math> has a local minimum at <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>&#8722;1</mn><mo>.</mo></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>&#8722;1</mn><mo>.</mo></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math> Since <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mi>f</mi></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mi>f</mi></annotation-xml></semantics></math> is increasing over the interval <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mrow><mo>(</mo><mrow><mn>&#8722;1</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow><mo>)</mo></mrow></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><mrow><mo>(</mo><mrow><mn>&#8722;1</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow><mo>)</mo></mrow></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math> and the interval <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mrow><mo>(</mo><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mo>)</mo></mrow><mo>,</mo></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><mrow><mo>(</mo><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mo>)</mo></mrow><mo>,</mo></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math> <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mi>f</mi></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mi>f</mi></annotation-xml></semantics></math> does not have a local extremum at <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math> Since <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mi>f</mi></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mi>f</mi></annotation-xml></semantics></math> is increasing over the interval <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mrow><mo>(</mo><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mo>)</mo></mrow></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><mrow><mo>(</mo><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mo>)</mo></mrow></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math> and decreasing over the interval <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mrow><mo>(</mo><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mi>&#8734;</mi></mrow><mo>)</mo></mrow><mo>,</mo><mi>f</mi></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><mrow><mo>(</mo><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mi>&#8734;</mi></mrow><mo>)</mo></mrow><mo>,</mo><mi>f</mi></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math> has a local maximum at <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math> The analytical results agree with the following graph.</p>
<figure id="CNX_Calc_Figure_04_05_004"><figcaption>The function <em data-effect="italics">f</em> has a local minimum at <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>&#8722;1</mn></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>&#8722;1</mn></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math> and a local maximum at <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math></figcaption>
<span data-type="media" id="fs-id1165043350494" data-alt="The function f(x) = 5x1/3 &#8211; x5/3 is graphed. It decreases to its local minimum at x = &#8722;1, increases to x = 1, and then decreases after that.">
