<div data-type="exercise" id="fs-id1165043321427">
<div data-type="problem" id="fs-id1165042946144">
<p id="fs-id1165042946146">For <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mi>f</mi><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mo>=</mo><mtext>&#8722;</mtext><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>18</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>,</mo></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><mi>f</mi><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mo>=</mo><mtext>&#8722;</mtext><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>18</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>,</mo></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math> find all intervals where <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mi>f</mi></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mi>f</mi></annotation-xml></semantics></math> is concave up and all intervals where <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mi>f</mi></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mi>f</mi></annotation-xml></semantics></math> is concave down.</p>
</div>
<div data-type="solution" id="fs-id1165042369707">
<p id="fs-id1165042369709"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mi>f</mi></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mi>f</mi></annotation-xml></semantics></math> is concave up over the interval <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mrow><mo>(</mo><mrow><mtext>&#8722;</mtext><mi>&#8734;</mi><mo>,</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mrow><mo>)</mo></mrow></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><mrow><mo>(</mo><mrow><mtext>&#8722;</mtext><mi>&#8734;</mi><mo>,</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mrow><mo>)</mo></mrow></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math> and concave down over the interval <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mrow><mo>(</mo><mrow><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>,</mo><mi>&#8734;</mi></mrow><mo>)</mo></mrow></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><mrow><mo>(</mo><mrow><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>,</mo><mi>&#8734;</mi></mrow><mo>)</mo></mrow></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math></p>
</div>
