<p id="fs-id1165043163933">We now summarize, in <a href="#fs-id1165043353366" class="autogenerated-content">[link]</a>, the information that the first and second derivatives of a function <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mi>f</mi></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mi>f</mi></annotation-xml></semantics></math> provide about the graph of <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mi>f</mi><mo>,</mo></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><mi>f</mi><mo>,</mo></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math> and illustrate this information in <a href="#CNX_Calc_Figure_04_05_008" class="autogenerated-content">[link]</a>.</p>
