<p id="fs-id1165043323993">For the following exercises, draw a graph that satisfies the given specifications for the domain <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mo stretchy="false">[</mo><mn>&#8722;3</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>3</mn><mo stretchy="false">]</mo><mo>.</mo></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mo stretchy="false">[</mo><mn>&#8722;3</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>3</mn><mo stretchy="false">]</mo><mo>.</mo></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math> The function does not have to be continuous or differentiable.</p>
<div data-type="exercise" id="fs-id1165042708286">
<div data-type="problem" id="fs-id1165042708288">
<p id="fs-id1165042708290"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mi>f</mi><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>,</mo><msup><mi>f</mi><mo>&#8242;</mo></msup><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><mi>f</mi><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>,</mo><msup><mi>f</mi><mo>&#8242;</mo></msup><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math> over <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>&#8722;3</mn><mo>&lt;</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>,</mo><msup><mi>f</mi><mo>&#8242;</mo></msup><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>&#8722;3</mn><mo>&lt;</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>,</mo><msup><mi>f</mi><mo>&#8242;</mo></msup><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math> over <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>&lt;</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>&lt;</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math></p>
