<p id="fs-id1165043219075">For the following exercises, consider a third-degree polynomial <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mi>f</mi><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mo>,</mo></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><mi>f</mi><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mo>,</mo></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math> which has the properties <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mrow><msup><mi>f</mi><mo>&#8242;</mo></msup><mrow><mo>(</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>)</mo></mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>,</mo><msup><mi>f</mi><mo>&#8242;</mo></msup><mrow><mo>(</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>)</mo></mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><msup><mi>f</mi><mo>&#8242;</mo></msup><mrow><mo>(</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>)</mo></mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>,</mo><msup><mi>f</mi><mo>&#8242;</mo></msup><mrow><mo>(</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>)</mo></mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math> Determine whether the following statements are <em data-effect="italics">true or false</em>. Justify your answer.</p><div data-type="exercise" id="fs-id1165043219135">
<div data-type="problem" id="fs-id1165043219137">
<p id="fs-id1165043219139"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mi>f</mi><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><mi>f</mi><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math> for some <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>&#8804;</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>&#8804;</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>&#8804;</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>&#8804;</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math></p>
